Message.MsgText: error.io.IOException.properties=CWUDV0014E: There was a problem reading from the properties file: {0}
Message.Explanation: An IO Exception was received when trying to read the properties file.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the properties file is readable and is in UTF-8 format.

Message.MsgText: error.io.unsupportedEncoding=CWUDV0015E: The value set data file {0} is in an unsupported encoding.
Message.Explanation: The value set file is not in UTF-8 format.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the file encoding format. See the Information Center information about user-defined value sets for more details.

Message.MsgText: error.dataFile.toManyTokens=CWUDV0009E: There were more fields than expected on line {0}: {1}
Message.Explanation: The line at the line number shown contains too many fields.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the line, or consider using a different column delimiter (-columnDelimiter).

Message.MsgText: message.checked=CWUDV1001W: The tModel with key {0} is checked. To confirm this operation, enter the command with the -override argument.
Message.Explanation: The targeted tModel has a status of checked, therefore you must use care if you change its value set.
Message.UserResponse: To confirm this operation, enter the command with the -override argument.

Message.MsgText: success.unload=CWUDV2003I: Unloaded value set for tModel key {0}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only. It confirms the removal of the value set for the tModel.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: error.unexpectedException=CWUDV0017E: An unexpected Exception has occurred.
Message.Explanation: An unexpected exception was detected.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the Exception stack trace to determine its cause.

Message.MsgText: error.dataFile.unterminatedString=CWUDV0007E: There is an unterminated string on line {0}: {1}
Message.Explanation: The line at the line number shown has a starting string delimiter, but not a finishing one.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the line, or consider using a different string delimiter (-stringDelimiter).

Message.MsgText: success.change=CWUDV2002I: Changed value set from tModel key {0} to tModel key {1}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only. It confirms the change of value set from one tModel to another.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: message.mBeanException=CWUDV1003W: UDDI Registry Message: {0}
Message.Explanation: A UDDI Registry message was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the message to determine its cause.

Message.MsgText: success.load=CWUDV2001I: Loaded {0} lines of data file for tModel key {1}.
Message.Explanation: This message is for informational purposes only. It confirms the number of value set lines loaded for the tModel.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: error.datafile.fieldTooLong=CWUDV0012E: The value set file contains a value ''{0}'' in column ''{1}'' at line {2} that is too long for the database table.
Message.Explanation: The value set data file contains a value that is too large.
Message.UserResponse: Decrease the size of the value. See the Information Center information about user-defined value sets for more details.

Message.MsgText: error.duplicateDelimiter=CWUDV0002E: The column and string delimiters must not be the same.
Message.Explanation: The column and string delimiters cannot be the same.
Message.UserResponse: Supply different characters for the column and string delimiters.

Message.MsgText: error.io.IOException=CWUDV0013E: An IO Exception has occurred: {0}
Message.Explanation: An IO Exception was received when trying to read the value set file.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the value set file is readable and is in UTF-8 format. See the Information Center information about user-defined value sets for more details.

Message.MsgText: error.unknownTModel=CWUDV0003E: A tModel for key {0} can not be found.
Message.Explanation: The tModel for the given key cannot be found.
Message.UserResponse: Supply a correct tModel key.

Message.MsgText: error.noUDDIMBean=CWUDV0016E: Unable to find the UDDI JMX MBean. Verify UDDI is installed.
Message.Explanation: The UDDI application could not be contacted.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that UDDI is installed and running on the host you have targeted. See the arguments -host, -port, -node, and -server.

Message.MsgText: error.dataFile.toFewTokens=CWUDV0008E: There were fewer fields than expected on line {0}: {1}
Message.Explanation: The line at the line number shown does not contain enough fields.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the line, or consider using a different column delimiter (-columnDelimiter).

Message.MsgText: error.datafile.duplicateKeyCode=CWUDV0010E: There is a duplicate Key Code at the same level on line {0}
Message.Explanation: The value set data file contains two or more codes of the same value with the same parent code.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the line. See the Information Center information about user-defined value sets for more details.

Message.MsgText: message.exists=CWUDV1002W: The tModel with key {0} has existing value sets. To confirm this operation, enter the command with the -override argument.
Message.Explanation: The targeted tModel to be loaded already has a value set.
Message.UserResponse: To confirm this operation and overwrite the existing value set, enter the command with the -override argument.

Message.MsgText: error.invalidArgument=CWUDV0004E: Invalid command arguments.
Message.Explanation: A command argument has been supplied that is unknown.
Message.UserResponse: Check your arguments with the usage information in the accompanying message.

Message.MsgText: error.datafile.notFound=CWUDV0006E: Unable to find the value set data file: {0}
Message.Explanation: The named value set file could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Supply the correct location of the value set file.

Message.MsgText: error.propertiesFile.notFound=CWUDV0001E: Unable to find the properties file: {0}
Message.Explanation: The named property file could not be located.
Message.UserResponse: Supply the correct location of the property file.

Message.MsgText: error.sameTModelKey=CWUDV0005E: Different tModel keys are required when using -newKey.
Message.Explanation: Two unique tModel keys are required to move a value set from one tModel to another.
Message.UserResponse: Supply two unique tModel keys.

Message.MsgText: error.datafile.invalidParentKeyCode=CWUDV0011E: An invalid Parent Key Code has been detected on line {0}
Message.Explanation: The value set data file contains a parent code that is invalid in its context.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the parent key code. See the Information Center information about user-defined value sets for more details.
